OL,5,CWAS IT WRONG TO FEED THE BIRDS?        
OL,7,CArthur Croft, 61,GfromCHammersmith,    
OL,8,GsaysGno-one should be stopped from     
OL,9,Gfeeding "harmless" birds.              
OL,10,G                                       
OL,11,G"People who are on their own,          
OL,12,Gparticularly older people, derive great
OL,13,Gpleasure from feeding birds. It sort of
OL,14,Cbreaks their isolation.                
OL,15,G                                       
OL,16,G"Preventing someone from doing that is 
OL,17,Ccruel,Gas it takes away the only       
OL,18,Gcomfort and joy they have."            
OL,19,G                                       
